cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this casebook in your work, please cite it as below."
title: "Digital-health survival casebook"
abstract: >-
  A worked casebook in survival and engagement analysis for a synthetic
  smoking-cessation digital-health cohort. Covers time-to-event modelling of
  quit and relapse, SMS re-engagement event studies, churn-risk prediction, and
  quit-anchored landmark analysis, with every generative parameter pinned to a
  published reference and recovered under parameter-recovery tests.
type: software
authors:
